A function is a set of instructions to perform a specific task.
The syntax of a function is the following

<Return type> <Name of the function> (Parameter(s) (optional)){
	Body of the function
}

If we don't want to return any type, the keyword used is "void". Example:

void print_twice(String message){
	System.out.println(message);
	System.out.println(message);
}

To use this function we "call" (or invoke) the function by it's name. For instance.

print_twice("Hello, there.")

11.2 Multiple parameters

11.3 Return type
We can return different values from a function. All the types seen in section 06 Class.
Example: Function that sums two numbers

int sumOfTwoNumbers(int firstNum, int secondNum){
	int sum = firstNum + secondNum;
	return sum;
}


Exercises.
1. Create a function that given a name, prints the following "Hello <name>"

2. Create a function that given two numbers, it returns the max number of them.

3. Create a function that given three scores, prints the average of them.

4. Given a number n, create a function that prints a number between 1 and n.

5. Create a function to print any multiplication table between 1 and 12